<!-- Location -->
<section id="location" class="about">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-12 text-center clear-bottom">
                <h2>Location &amp; Times</h2>
                <p>If you want to stay over in the local area for the wedding, there are various accommodation options.</p>
                <p>The most convenient accommodation is onsite at Bisham Abbey. At the time of writing, this is also the cheapest. However, there is a limited number of rooms available, so if you want to take this option, we recommend you book soon.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-6 text-center clear-bottom">
                <img id="logo" class="featureImage" src="/img/circle_church.png" alt="" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <h3>Ceremony</h3>
                <p>The wedding ceremony is at <b>12:15 on 7th April 2018</b> at <b>Bisham Church, SL7 1RW</b></p>
                <p>Parking: We have arranged for use of the co-located <b>Bisham School</b> car park. This should provide ample parking for all guests. The school and church are clearly signposted from the main road. Once you have turned off the main road, turn immediately right through the school gates. Continue round to the front of the school for extended parking.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-6 text-center">
                <img id="logo" class="featureImage" src="/img/circle_abbey.png" alt="" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6">
                <h3>Reception</h3>
                <p>The reception will be following the ceremony and is at <b>Bisham Abbey National Sport Centre</b>.</p>
                <p>Bisham Church and Abbey are neighbors. However as the Abbey grounds are quite large, the drive or walk along the road is around 900m. It is possible to cut across the Abbey grounds, however the grass is often wet and muddy, so not recommended; especially for high heels!</p>
                <p>There will be a meal at around 15:30. The menu has not yet been formalised. We will email you when this is available. However, if you have any requirements (such as vegetarian food), please include this on your RSVP.</p>
                <p>There will be light food and a ceilidh in the evening.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- /.container -->
</section>

